snippet.title: Meghan, The Duchess of Sussex’s New Children’s Book Started as a Poem to Her Husband
snippet.description:
Meghan, The Duchess of Sussex talked about her New York Times bestselling children’s book, “The Bench,” which originally started out as a poem for her husband, Prince Harry, The Duke of Sussex. The activist also talked about fighting for paid family leave in America, what she liked to do when she was growing up in Los Angeles, and how she once had a haircut that resembled “The Simpsons” character, Krusty the Clown!
